KANO â€“ A Magistrate Court in Kano on Friday granted bail to Abdulmajid Danbilki Kwamanda who is standing trial over alleged defamation of the personality of Kano State Governor, Dr Abdullahi Umar Ganduje in the radio interview. The Court presided over by Senior Magistrate, Aminu Gabari admitted the accused person to the sum of N1million, and two reliable sureties in the like sum. Magistrate Gabari ordered that the surety shall be Chief Imam of Mariya Dantata Mosque, Koki and Wakilan Gabas, Kano Emirate. The court also ordered that the two sureties must have 5 years tax clearance. Similarly, it ordered that the defendant should deposit his international passport to the court registry.